Quickstart (copy/paste)

Create repo directory and add files above.

Edit config.yaml and samples.tsv to point to your files.

Create environment:

conda env create -f environment.yml
conda activate ribo_env


Run pipeline:

bash scripts/00_download_geo.sh config.yaml    # optional: download data
bash scripts/01_trim_and_rRNA_removal.sh config.yaml
bash scripts/02_align_star.sh config.yaml
Rscript scripts/03_psite_riboWaltz.R config.yaml
bash scripts/04_orf_detection.sh config.yaml
python3 scripts/05_pause_detection.py
bash scripts/06_counts_featureCounts.sh config.yaml
Rscript scripts/07_deseq2_TE.R config.yaml


Open analysis/RiboSeq_DESeq2_TE_Analysis.Rmd and knit to view plots & tables.
